pan class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Opposites.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.op\">op</a></span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.comp\">comp</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nonempty\">Nonempty</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/IsLimit.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.IsLimit\">Limits.IsLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">data</span> <span class=\"fn\">X</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/DenseSubsite/OneHypercoverDense.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.OneHypercoverDenseData.toOneHypercover\">toOneHypercover</a></span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Hypercover/One.html#CategoryTheory.PreOneHypercover.multifork\">multifork</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `F : C₀ ⥤ C` be a dense subsite, and assume we have a family\n`data : ∀ X, F.OneHypercoverDenseData J₀ J X`.\nThis lemma shows that `G : Cᵒᵖ ⥤ A` is a sheaf iff `F.op F.op ⋙ G : C₀ᵒᵖ ⥤ A`\nis a sheaf and for any `X : C`, the multifork for `G` and the `1`-hypercover\ngiven by `data X` is a limit. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/DenseSubsite/OneHypercoverDense.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.OneHypercoverDenseData.isSheaf_iff","kind":"theorem","line":403,"name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.OneHypercoverDenseData.isSheaf_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/DenseSubsite/OneHypercoverDense.lean#L403-L416"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"b